column3: feature_definition
Concentration of S-sulfocysteine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.
Concentration of DOPA (3,4-dihydroxyphenylalanine) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.
A developmental anomnaly characterized by the lack of development of the posterior communicating artery.
The concentration of guanidinoacetic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.
An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the eyelid.
The presence of a nodule (small rounded lump of tissue) in the iris.
Accumulation of antigen-bound antibody in the skin.
Enzyme activity of aromatase below the lower limit of normal.
Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by administration of phenytoin.

column2: Altered location of the longitudinal column in the fibrous sheath
column3: The fibrous sheath is a structure in the midpiece of the sperm flagellum surrounding the outer dense fibers. It comprises two longitudinal columns and tranverse ribs. In case of altered location of the longitudinal column in the fibrous sheath the symmetrical structure is lost, most commonly with the columns not being opposite to each other, which can be visualised by electron microscopy.

column2: Entamoeba histolytica antibody positive in stool
column3: Demonstration of antibody directed against Entamoeba histolytica in stool.
Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with thiamine.
Amount of keratin 14 in the epidermis below the lower limit of normal. The findiong is typically ascertained by immunofluorescent microscopy.
A history of following a vegan diet characterized by avoidance of food sourced from animals including meet, fish, and dairy products.
Any structural anomaly of the keratinocyte. The keratinocyte is the major cell type of the epidermis and is responsible for generating the protective barrier.
Sharply angled insertion of the neck and midpiece into the head of a spermatozoon. This term applies if the proportion of spermatozoa with this feature is above the upper limit of normal.
Information about current or past medications taken by an individual.

Concentration of glutathione in red blood cells below the lower limit of normal. Glutathione (GSH) is an important redox active biomolecule critical in the maintenance and regulation of cellular and organismal health.
The presence of inclusion bodies within the cytoplasm of muscle cells that contain a mxiture of granules and filaments.
A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to cytarabine.
Lymph node with increased numbers of macrophages heavily laden with lipids.
History of having taken a calcium channel blocker such as amlodipine, nicardipine, nifedipine, verapamil, or diltiazem.

column2: Asymmetrical insertion of the midpiece into the head
column3: Insertion of the neck and midpiece into the head of a spermatozoon on an axis that diverges from the midline axis of the spermatozoon head. This term applies if the proportion of spermatozoa with this defect is above the upper limit of normal.
A break or tear in the trachea.
The mother of a fetus or index patient has a history of hyperthyroidism during the corresponding pregnancy.

column2: Reduced epidermal bullous pemphigoid antigen 1 protein expression
column3: Lower than normal amount of bullous pemphigoid antigen 1 (BP230) in the epidermis.
Eruption of permanent teeth behind deciduous (baby) teeth before they have fallen out, resulting in a double row of teeth. This phenomen is typically observed between the ages of 5 to 7 years.
Deposition of a largely amorphous hyaline (transparent and homogeneous) substance around blood vessels in the wall of the small intestine.

Diminished activity of the enzyme enolase in muscle tissue. The enzyme enolase catalyzes the interconversion of 2-phosphoglycerate and phosphoenolpyruvate. In adult human muscle, over 90% of enolase activity is accounted for by the beta-enolase subunit, the protein product of the ENO3 gene.
Concentration of apolipoprotein E above the upper limit of normal.
Occuring on the left and right in succession. This term can refer to alternating sides of the body (e.g., Alternating hemiplegia) or alternative sides of the visual field (e.g., some migraine auras).
The concentration of norepinephrine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.
Concentration of norepinephrin in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.
A structural abnormality of the knee joint or surrounding structures.

Abnormal structure of the rete ridges (also known as rete pegs), which are
downward projections of epithelium surrounding the connective tissue papillae in between the dermal papillae.
Concentration or activity of an arylsulfatase C as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal in the blood circulation.
Width of the cavum septum pellucidum above the upper limit of normal, which is defined as a separation of greater than one cm of the leaves of the cavum septum pellucidum.

column2: Abnormal leukocyte enzyme concentration or activity
column3: Concentration or activity of an enzyme as measured in leukocytes is above or below the limits of normal in the blood circulation.
Downward pointing exostoses of the occipital bone situated in the tendinous insertions of the sternocleidomastoid and trapezius muscles.
Accumulation of monoclonal CD1a-positive Langerhans cells in the bronchioles and alveolar interstitium that can cause damage to the lungs.
The concentration of formiminoglutamic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
Concentration of antidiuretic hormone, also known as vasopressin, is below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation.
A gastrinoma, a neuroendocrine tumors characterized by the secretion of gastrin with resultant excessive gastric acid production, that is localized to the duodenum.
The concentration of epinephrine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.
Amount of erythritol in the urine above the upper limit of normal.
Excessive proliferation of fibroblasts and deposition of extracellular matrix within the ovary.
A highly aggressive, extremely rare neoplasm of the ovary that is usually seen in children. The term rhabdoid is used because the tumor cells resemble rhabdomyoblasts but lack myogenic markers.
Lack of observable peroxisomes. This feature can be observed by immunohistochemical staining of cultured cells (such as fibroblasts) or by electronmicroscopy.
